    <fr:title text="Fibre products of schemes are topological">Fibre products of schemes are topological</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Theorem</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter><html:p>
  Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X,Y,S]]></fr:tex> be <fr:link href="/schm-86OJ/" title="Scheme" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-86OJ/" display-uri="schm-86OJ" type="local">schemes</fr:link> with morphisms <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f : X \to  S]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g : Y \to  S]]></fr:tex>. Then the pullback <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X \times _S Y]]></fr:tex> exists in the category of schemes, and its underlying topological space is the pullback in the category of topological spaces.
</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>6</fr:month><fr:day>11</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  <html:p>
    The existence of the fibre products follows from the usual gluing argument for schemes in algebraic geometry, and reduces to the fibre products of affine schemes, which by <fr:link href="/schm-X3M9/" title="Universal property of spectra" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-X3M9/" display-uri="schm-X3M9" type="local">Theorem <fr:contextual-number uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-X3M9/" display-uri="schm-X3M9" /></fr:link> are computed by spectra of <fr:link href="/idem-comm-SG6C/" title="Tensor products of distributive lattices" uri="https://charloced.github.io/idem-comm-SG6C/" display-uri="idem-comm-SG6C" type="local">tensor products</fr:link>.
  </html:p>
  <html:p>
    To show the fibre products are topological, we first show this for affine schemes. In this case, the fibre products are computed by the spectrum of <fr:link href="/idem-comm-A6ON/" title="Pushouts of algebras are tensor products" uri="https://charloced.github.io/idem-comm-A6ON/" display-uri="idem-comm-A6ON" type="local">pushouts</fr:link>. The underlying set is the topological fibre products, because the points are computed by <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {DL}(-,2)]]></fr:tex>, which takes pushouts to pullbacks. The topology also agrees due to our pushouts are concretely constructed as <fr:link href="/idem-comm-SG6C/" title="Tensor products of distributive lattices" uri="https://charloced.github.io/idem-comm-SG6C/" display-uri="idem-comm-SG6C" type="local">tensor product</fr:link>.
  </html:p>
  <html:p>
    Now the general case for schemes follows from glueing.
  </html:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
