            <fr:title text="Pushouts of algebras are tensor products">Pushouts of algebras are tensor products</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Proposition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>
  Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A,B]]></fr:tex> be two <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[D]]></fr:tex>-algebras. Then the <fr:link href="/idem-comm-SG6C/" title="Tensor products of distributive lattices" uri="https://charloced.github.io/idem-comm-SG6C/" display-uri="idem-comm-SG6C" type="local">tensor product</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A \otimes _D B]]></fr:tex> is the pushout in <html:strong>DL</html:strong>:
  
  <html:figure><fr:resource hash="9b3f00e1f4661f9bb4dd724a5da45f3d"><fr:resource-content><html:img src="/9b3f00e1f4661f9bb4dd724a5da45f3d.svg" /></fr:resource-content><fr:resource-source type="latex" part="preamble"><![CDATA[\usepackage {tikz-cd}\usepackage {quiver}]]></fr:resource-source><fr:resource-source type="latex" part="body"><![CDATA[
    \begin {tikzcd}
      D \ar [r, "f"] \ar [d, "g"'] & A \ar [d] \\ 
      B \ar [r] & A \otimes _D B
      \arrow [{"\lrcorner "{anchor = center, pos = 0.125, rotate=180}, draw = none, from=2-2, to=1-1}]
    \end {tikzcd}
  ]]></fr:resource-source></fr:resource></html:figure></html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>6</fr:month><fr:day>11</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  Given <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[u : A \to  C]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[v : B \to  C]]></fr:tex> with <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[uf = vg]]></fr:tex>, we construct a map 
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[ [u,v] : A \otimes _D B \to  C ]]></fr:tex>
  by sending a generator <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a \otimes  b]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[ua \wedge  vb]]></fr:tex>. We need to show this respects the congruence of the <fr:link href="/idem-comm-SG6C/" title="Tensor products of distributive lattices" uri="https://charloced.github.io/idem-comm-SG6C/" display-uri="idem-comm-SG6C" type="local">tensor product</fr:link>:
  <html:ol><html:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[[u,v](a \otimes  0) = ua \wedge  v0 = 0 = [u,v]]]></fr:tex>, and similarly for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[0 \otimes  b]]></fr:tex>. </html:li>
    <html:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[[u,v](a \vee  a' \otimes  b) = u(a \vee  a') \wedge  vb = (ua \wedge  vb) \vee  (ua' \wedge  vb) = [u,v](a \otimes  b \vee  a' \otimes  b)]]></fr:tex>, and similarly for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a \otimes  b\vee  b']]></fr:tex>.</html:li>
    <html:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[[u,v][aa' \otimes  bb'] = u(aa') \wedge  v(bb') = ua \wedge  ua' \wedge  vb \wedge  vb' = [u,v](a\otimes  b \wedge  a' \otimes  b')]]></fr:tex>. </html:li>
    <html:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[[u,v](ad \otimes  b) = ua \wedge  ufd \wedge  vb = ua \wedge  vgd \wedge  vb = [u,v](a \otimes  db)]]></fr:tex>. </html:li></html:ol>
  Hence, the map <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[[u,v]]]></fr:tex> is well-defined, and in fact uniquely determined by the two inclusions <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A \to  A \otimes _DB]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B \to  A \otimes _DB]]></fr:tex>.
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
